		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So the real resolution is exactly 35/32 times the amount of visible pixels?</div>
<br />That depends on your TV. Different brands of TV cut off different amounts of the sides of the screen. But if you want the picture to be the same width as that of the NES, Genesis, or Super NES, then yes, the visible picture is 32/35 = 91.4% of the <a href="http://lurkertech.com/lg/video-systems/#480i_sq_sampling" class="postlink">clean aperture</a>.

		

		</td>
